last_episode_to_air.name: Take a Back Road
last_episode_to_air.overview: A comic celebration of the mundane peak-hour ritual for workers of despatch centre K2, dealing with a US takeover and the appointment of a new CEO, a prodigious leader doing everything she can to disguise the human within.

name: Squinters
overview: The trials and tribulations of car loads of travellers in peak hour morning transit and again on their drive home to find out how the workday turned out.

episodes.name: Hit The Road
episodes.overview: Paul starts a carpool and invites Romi from Marketing. Lukas' promotion turns into a redundancy. Ned reveals Macca was his school yard bully, Talia is hired as Simoni's supervisor and Mia crushes Bridget's cool mum status.

episodes.name: Rocky Road
episodes.overview: Paul paints Romi a portrait. Lukas avoids criminal negligence but not a civil suit. Bridget lies to suitor Garry about having kids, burns her lip prepping for a date. Talia reveals the truth behind her interview success.

episodes.name: King Of The Road
episodes.overview: Ned finds out his wife slept with his best mate, Romi kisses Paul, Lukas considers his redundancy offer, Simoni has gotten over her resentment of Talia's supervisor job and Garry's future with Bridget comes under threat.

episodes.name: Road to Nowhere
episodes.overview: Paul wishes he didn't bring up the kiss and Eric leaves Lukas, again. Macca gets laid, Mia compiles a list of Garry's pros and cons and Simoni is surprised by the cost of virgin hair.

episodes.name: Crossroads
episodes.overview: Romi contemplates becoming a delivery driver, Paul gives her pet names and Barney shags Daisey's brother. Macca re-invites Ned to his buck's party, Bridget ghosts Garry and Talia discovers Simoni knows all her passwords.

episodes.name: End of the Road
episodes.overview: Paul misses Romi's confession and Lukas guilts Miles to convert mum's remains into a diamond. No one shows for Macca's buck's party, Bridget and Mia have a pregnancy scare and Talia considers chilling in gaol.

episodes.name: On the Road Again
episodes.overview: Talia ditches Simoni for Romi after their yoga wine bar collapse, Lukas works Aunty Alison to access his Mum's will and Bridget is outed as racist. Macca wants a baby and new CEO Tina grapples with Australian driver Brett.

episodes.name: A Winding Road
episodes.overview: Talia avoids the debt collectors, Lukas' frustrations force thoughts of murder and Bridget is nervous ahead of meeting Gary's parents. Jess protects her unborn baby's ears and Tina fires Brett after an uncomfortable moment.

episodes.name: Roadhouse Blues
episodes.overview: Talia struggles to break a cycle of lying, Macca misreads a text from a work colleague while Lukas bonds with fellow fork lifter. Gary turns on Bridget and Tina worries her employees hate her, despite warning them of danger.

episodes.name: Thunder Roar
episodes.overview: Romi and Talia's parents use each other, while Macca's workmate pranks his cake. Lukas can't convert his workmate, Bridget feigns sickness and Tina denies intimacy.

episodes.name: Bless the Broken Road
episodes.overview: Talia donates eggs and Gav donates sperm to Macca and Jess's IVF effort. Lukas seeks evidence against Alison, Gary fears he's become his dad and Tina is dismissed by headquarters for warning employees about asbestos.

episodes.name: Take a Back Road
episodes.overview: A comic celebration of the mundane peak-hour ritual for workers of despatch centre K2, dealing with a US takeover and the appointment of a new CEO, a prodigious leader doing everything she can to disguise the human within.
